"""
Farsite fuel-parameter table for ForeFire, extended with a non-burnable barrier.

This is ForeFire's built-in STDfarsiteFuelsTable (from SimulationParameters.cpp,
keyed by LANDFIRE FBFM40 indices 101–204) with one extra row appended:

    index 999 = a NON-BURNABLE BARRIER used for water/urban/rock cells.

We can't use the raster's real non-burnable codes (91–99) directly: those have a
fuel-bed depth of 0, and the Farsite rate-of-spread calc divides by depth, which
yields NaN and corrupts the fire front. The barrier row instead has a tiny load
and a small nonzero depth (so no division by zero) plus a moisture of extinction
(0.005) far below any real fuel moisture, which forces the reaction — and thus
the rate of spread — cleanly to zero. Fire simply stops at these cells.
"""

